cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses unsupervised learning of semantic mappings, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus on neural networks and their complexity suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of image and text data also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the use of neural networks and the focus on optimization suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
